See my blog post on this demo: https://www.dzombak.com/blog/2021/10/HTTPS-Requests-with-a-Root-Certificate-Store-on-ESP8266-Arduino.html

---

HTTP(S) demo specific notes:
- https://arduino-esp8266.readthedocs.io/en/latest/esp8266wifi/bearssl-client-secure-class.html
  recommends running at 160MHz, which is accomplished in platformio.ini
- A lot of online tutorials recommend hardcoding a certificate fingerprint; I wanted to
  use an actual certificate store.
- Upload `data` (certificate store) to board's LittleFS via `platformio run --target uploadfs` 
  from the project root directory.

References:
- https://arduino-esp8266.readthedocs.io/en/latest/esp8266wifi/bearssl-client-secure-class.html
- https://github.com/esp8266/Arduino/blob/master/libraries/ESP8266WiFi/examples/BearSSL_CertStore/BearSSL_CertStore.ino
- https://medium.com/@dfa_31434/doing-ssl-requests-on-esp8266-correctly-c1f60ad46f5e
- https://www.instructables.com/Using-ESP8266-SPIFFS/
